article.description: Whitney Boddie had 13 points, 10 rebounds and 12 assists for her first career triple-double, and Auburn (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) routed Sam Houston State 119-54 on Friday night.
article.headline: Boddie's first career triple-double helps Auburn rout Sam Houston
article.linkText: Boddie's triple-double fuels No. 13 Auburn's rout
article.story:
AUBURN, Ala. -- Whitney Boddie had 13 points, 10 rebounds and 12 assists for her first career triple-double, and Auburn (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) routed Sam Houston State 119-54 on Friday night.

KeKe Carrier added 19 points on 9-of-9 shooting, and DeWanna Bonner had 18 points for the Tigers (9-0), who set a school record for points in a game. Auburn shot 62 percent compared to the Bearkats' 31 percent, while forcing 26 turnovers and getting 56 points off the bench.

Seven Auburn players scored in double figures, including Chantel Hilliard and Reneisha Hobbs, who finished with 13 points apiece. Everyone that got in the game scored for the Tigers.

Mary Beth Renz led the Bearkats (1-7) with 12 points.
